# GNU Image Manipulation Program

media-gfx/gimp aalib alsa -altivec -aqua bzip2 curl dbus -debug doc exif -gnome jpeg jpeg2k lcms mng openexr pdf png postscript -python smp svg tiff udev webkit wmf xpm

# aalib		Add support for media-libs/aalib (ASCII-Graphics Library)
# alsa		Add support for media-libs/alsa-lib (Advanced Linux Sound Architecture)
# altivec	Add support for optimizations for G4 and G5/ppc970 processors
# aqua		Include support for the Mac OS X Aqua (Carbon/Cocoa) GUI
# bzip2		Use the bzlib compression library
# curl		Add support for client-side URL transfer library
# dbus		Enable dbus support for anything that needs it
# debug		Enable extra debug codepaths, like asserts and extra output.
# doc		Add extra documentation (API, Javadoc, etc).
# exif		Add support for reading EXIF headers from JPEG and TIFF images
# gnome		Add GNOME support
# jpeg		Add JPEG image support
# jpeg2k	Support for JPEG 2000, a wavelet-based image compression format
# lcms		Add lcms support (color management engine)
# mng		Add support for libmng (MNG images)
# openexr	Support for the OpenEXR graphics file format
# pdf		Add general support for PDF (Portable Document Format), this replaces 
# png		Add support for libpng (PNG images)
# postscript	Enable support for the PostScript language (often with ghostscript-gpl
# python	Add optional support/bindings for the Python language
# smp		Enable support for multiprocessors
# svg		Add support for SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics)
# tiff		Add support for the TIFF image format
# udev		Enable virtual/udev integration (device discovery, power and storage d
# webkit	Add support for the WebKit HTML rendering/layout engine
# wmf		Add support for the Windows Metafile vector image format
# xpm		Add support for XPM graphics format
